  "articleSummary": "The article argues that AngularJS v1.x can remain enjoyable only if developers curb the over‑use of `$watch` and `$scope` by keeping UI state minimal and limiting directive depth. It presents a tutorial‑style guide that demonstrates how to refactor a bulky user‑widget into a leaner component, recommends one‑way bindings, avoiding nested directives inside `ng‑repeat`, and using factories for low‑level DOM work, while also suggesting Browserify for dependency management. The piece is aimed at intermediate AngularJS developers who maintain medium‑to‑large applications and balances practical tips with a light‑hearted, cautionary tone that repeatedly frames Angular’s features as “weapons” that can become burdensome when mis‑applied.",
